18:26.540 --> 18:36.300
least one unpronounceable word in each title, will let her tell you what she's
written in the fantasy and science fiction genres? In 1979, Doubleday published

18:36.300 --> 18:54.040
How the Gods Wole in Kiranok. In 80, Doubleday brought out The Seekers of
Sharnung. In 81, 81 brought Soul Singer of Tearno from Athenaeum. 82, Busted

18:54.040 --> 19:02.100
Loose Like a Pot of Popcorn. Warlock's Gift came from Doubleday in the spring.

19:04.920 --> 19:10.840
Paperback reprints from Ace of How the Gods Wole in Seekers of Sharnung came out
that spring.

19:14.020 --> 19:18.120
Bruise of the Liar came out from Athenaeum that fall.

19:20.820 --> 19:34.020
And Golden Dream, A Fuzzy Odyssey came out. That's all. So it sort of just
grabbed you up like a tornado and carried you away spinning. We asked Mayhar

19:34.020 --> 19:47.080
what type of fantasy she writes. It is really more towards heroic fantasy.
Though not in the sword and sorcery type of thing. These are more people who are

19:47.080 --> 20:01.080
heroic, not through physical strength or anything like that, but because of the
press of circumstance and integrity. I try to write about the way people can be

20:01.080 --> 20:16.540
and often are. Real urban is fine. I mean, there's a place for that. But I have
never seen that the cause of human enlightenment has been forwarded too much by

20:16.540 --> 20:31.800
depicting the absolute worst aspects of human nature. People can be noble. They
can be courageous. And they very often are, so why not write about it? Since she

20:31.800 --> 20:44.620
is a poet as well, we asked Mayhar if writing poetry helps her write prose. I
talk to a lot of college classes, and I belong to a group that has beginners in

20:44.620 --> 20:58.060
it. And I tell them, write poetry even if it's bad poetry, because in poetry you
don't have a novel's worth of elbow room. You can't use 25 wrong words to get

20:58.060 --> 21:04.120
across an idea that two perfect words will give with punch, you know, with real
impact.

21:06.800 --> 21:19.240
Poetry takes the laziness out of it. It makes you search for the proper words,
the proper phrases, exact construction. It conveys what you want to give. Mayhar

21:19.240 --> 21:27.860
published her first novel after her children have come. We asked her if she ever
wishes she had gotten published earlier. You know, I have given that a lot of

21:27.860 --> 21:40.520
thought. It's a very rough road to hold. But I have come to the conclusion that
people who have a great deal of success, they're young, quite often don't keep

21:40.520 --> 21:51.780
pushing themselves to refine their technique, get better and better and better,
so that, by golly, you are so good they can't turn you down. Besides which, you

21:51.780 --> 22:05.340
know, when you live 40 years, you know a lot of things you didn't know when you
lived 25 years. You understand not only what people do, but how they feel under

22:05.340 --> 22:15.980
different circumstances. When a husband comes home and he's lost his job, you
not only know how he acts, you know how he and his wife feel about it. And this

22:15.980 --> 22:28.060
is something that I think causes a great deal of modern non-genre fiction to be
superficial. People are writing about it who have never stood in those shoes and

22:28.060 --> 22:38.580
who don't really understand what it does to your gut to have a child get deathly
ill at 2 o'clock in the morning. You know, all this sort of thing. We'll have

22:38.580 --> 22:40.360
more with Ardeth Mayhar on our next show.

