miserable every minute. Oh, I had to live in Houston for 16 months. I thought

27:58.900 --> 28:11.900
I'd die. In fact, I think I would have died if we hadn't left. We've always had
a little plot of ground. Maybe not for two acres, but something. We've always

28:11.900 --> 28:21.460
had some kind of livestock. When spring comes, if I can't get my hands in the
dirt and make a garden, you just better buy a straight jacket and call the men

28:21.460 --> 28:31.840
in the white coats because I'm ready to go off. I do my best writing, thinking
in the garden. Or even milking the cow. You know, the old head just keeps

28:31.840 --> 28:32.860
rolling right along.

